# Project Rules

## Package Manager

This project uses **Bun** as the package manager and runtime. Always use `bun` instead of `npm`, `yarn`, or `pnpm`.

### Commands

| Instead of          | Use                  |
| ------------------- | -------------------- |
| `npm install`       | `bun install`        |
| `npm install <pkg>` | `bun add <pkg>`      |
| `npm install -D`    | `bun add -d <pkg>`   |
| `npm run <script>`  | `bun run <script>`   |
| `npm test`          | `bun test`           |
| `npm ci`            | `bun install --frozen-lockfile` |

### Examples

```bash
# Install dependencies
bun install

# Add a new dependency
bun add react-query

# Add a dev dependency
bun add -d vitest

# Run scripts
bun run dev
bun run build
bun run typecheck
```

## Styling

This project uses **vanilla-extract** for type-safe CSS-in-JS styling with design tokens.

- Design tokens are defined in `app/styles/tokens.css.ts`
- Global styles are in `app/styles/global.css.ts`
- Component styles should be in `.css.ts` files colocated with components
- Import tokens using `import { vars } from "~/styles"`
